<TEXT>
<P>
It's tacky, tacky, tacky for NBC to show the preempted episodes of "Miami Vice" 
after the series-ending episode on May 21. This is like the Dodgers playing 
rained-out games after the World Series! Like George Bush giving campaign 
speeches after the election! Like "The Winds of War" showing the last episode 
before the middle episodes! 
</P>
<P>
It's very thoughtless of NBC to show "Miami Vice" out of sequence. And it's not 
very nice. "Miami Vice" used to be a big hit for NBC and it's a shame the 
network is letting the show go out in a schlocky fashion. 
</P>
<P>
Linda Cowan Mose, Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
