<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAFE AND SOUND NO MORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for "Safe and Sound No More," by John Doyle (April 23). I am a mother 
of a 2-year-old. My house is baby-proofed, my 6-foot wrought-iron fence around 
my pool is locked, and I never let my child out of my sight in public places. 
These are things I was told to look for to keep my child from harm. Now I know 
from Doyle's very painful article to look for more than the obvious. 
</P>
<P>
I'm very sorry this happened to his children -- but I am so thankful he shared 
this story that other children may be spared. 
</P>
<P>
MRS. ROBERT SCHILLER 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
