<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUMMER SPLASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Think again about the "Pirates of the Caribbean" at Disneyland, which the 
Summer Splash section of May 28 described as a "perfect fantasy-kingdom." Are 
there many women, husbands and fathers whose fantasies include the slave/bride 
auctions depicted in this "champion of Disneyland attractions" -- auctions that 
resulted in rapes? 
</P>
<P>
The reviewer's mention of a ride with scenes inspired by the film "Song of the 
South" makes me hope that racism won't follow sexism as a Disney-approved value 
for entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
CAROL PRZYBYCIEN 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
