<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE HOUSING CHIEF TAKES POST WITH BUILDERS GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Christine Diemer Reed, California's top government housing official, will take 
over as executive director of an Orange County builders trade group on July 1. 
</P>
<P>
Reed, 36, will succeed John Erskine as head of the Orange County region of the 
Building Industry Assn. of Southern California. Erskine announced earlier this 
year that he was joining a local law firm. 
</P>
<P>
Reed was appointed head of the state Department of Housing and Community 
Development by Gov. George Deukmejian in 1986. She had previously served as a 
deputy attorney general and as deputy secretary for housing in the California 
business, transportation and housing agency. 
</P>
<P>
Reed is married to Dana Reed, a partner in the prominent Costa Mesa-based law 
firm of Reed &amp; Davidson. 
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 builders, developers and other businesses belong to the BIA's 
Orange County region, according to an official with the trade group. It has 
played a key role in shaping the course of development in several Southland 
areas, but perhaps is best known for being a linchpin in the business 
community's successful efforts to beat back the slow-growth Measure A on last 
year's Orange County ballots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
