<P>
PLUNGE OFF BRIDGE CLAIMS 2ND VICTIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The passenger of a vehicle that catapulted off the Sunset Cliffs Bridge into 
the San Diego River, killing the driver, died Friday night of injuries suffered 
in the crash. 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego County Coroner's office identified the driver Saturday as Steven 
Wayne Epeneter, 34, a drywall carpenter who lived in the 4800 block of Penrose 
Court in San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
His passenger was identified as Noelle Christine Meier, 21, who lived in the 
4900 block of September Street and was a student at UC San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said Epeneter was southbound early Friday morning at high speed 
when he lost control of his vehicle, which crashed through the bridge railing 
into the water below. 
</P>
