An officer wearing a bullet-proof vest was slightly injured when the suspect 
fired a shotgun blast at him before being arrested, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Another man was wounded Friday night after he allegedly fired at officers in 
South-Central Los Angeles, authorities said. Sheriff's deputies said Manuel 
James Earles, 18, was in serious condition after they shot him when he opened 
fire on an anti-gang task force that was trying to question him. 
