<P>
Favored Aliysa broke away from the field in the final two furlongs to win the 
English Oaks turf race for fillies in near-record time at Epsom, England. 
</P>
<P>
Aliysa, the 11-10 choice ridden by Walter Swinburn, stumbled coming out of the 
gate and was boxed in along the rail for much of the race. But she sped past 
front-running Mamaluna in the final straight and won by three lengths over Snow 
Bride. 
</P>
<P>
Aliysa's time of 2:34.22 was only one-hundredth of a second off the Oaks record 
set by Time Charter in 1982. 
