<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASSENGER KILLED WHEN TRUCK FLIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old man was killed early Saturday when the truck he was riding in 
overturned on the on-ramp from Camino Capistrano to northbound Interstate 5 in 
San Juan Capistrano, according to the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Andrew Sanchez of San Juan Capistrano was crushed to death when the truck 
flipped over and fell into a ditch about 2:45 a.m., CHP officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The pickup's driver, identified by the CHP as Raul Macias of San Juan 
Capistrano, was arrested on suspicion of felony drunk driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
