<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 COUNTY RESIDENTS WIN IN 'BIG SPIN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Orange County residents were among the 14 winners of the state lottery's 
"Big Spin" contest held Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Rhonda Johns, 21, a Buena Park nursing assistant, won $50,000 and Darryl 
Chamberlain, 40, a La Habra data processor, won $30,000. 
</P>
<P>
The two biggest winners Saturday were Stephen Jacobson, 26, of La Mesa, and 
Kenneth Hildreth, 47, of Yuba City. Each won $1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
